==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/geld/}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛld|-ɛld]]

===Etymology 1===
Medieval Latin ''[[geldum]]'', Old English ''[[gield]]'', "payment", "tribute". Confer Dutch '''[[#Dutch|geld]]''', "money", German ''[[Geld]]'', "money", Old Norse ''[[giald]]'', "payment", Gothic ''[[gild]]'', "tribute". Also confer "[[yield]]". '''Geld''' is also written '''gelt''', or '''gild''', and as such found in "[[Danegelt]]", and "[[wergild]]".

====Noun====
'''geld'''
# [[money]]; [[tribute]]; [[compensation]]; [[ransom]].

===Etymology 2===
Confer the German, dialectal words ''[[gelten]]'', "to geld", and ''[[gelze]]'', "castrated swine". Hence "[[gelding]]"

====Verb====
{{en-verb}}

# {{transitive}} To [[castrate]] a [[male]] (usually an [[animal]]).

